review_res.text: I always start with the fruit named A and compare it to B to see which one is heavier. Then, I compare the lower of the 2 (B,A) to each remaining letter. I put heavier fruits on the right and lighter fruits on the left. Then I start with a new letter and compare to all others left.
r_question:
Shortly describe your approach of the PURPLE DIAMOND for arranging

a SMALLER pile of fruits (shown on right)

in increasing weights from left to right? (180 secs to answer)

review_res.text: I do it the same way as I would the smaller set of fruits, it just takes longer and I use more comparisons.
r_question:
Shortly describe your approach of the PURPLE DIAMOND for arranging

a LARGER pile of fruits (shown on right)

in increasing weights from left to right? (180 secs to answer)

review_res.text: If I have two fruits that are the heaviest out of them all, then I compare those 2 first and see which is heaviest. Then I start with the next two in line
